          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>ב"ה באלטימארע יום ה' תרנ"ז אסתר תבר"ק לפ"ק</add>
                              </p>
                              <p><placeName>Barnet St No 26</placeName>.</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>לידיד נפשי המופלא בחכמה ובמעשים כ"ה יצחק אלעשר שם
                                                  שוכטס</add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName>,
                                                  <date>Thursday, Fast of
                                        Esther,<lb/>1852</date></p>
                              <p>To my dear friend, etc., <sic><addressee>Rabbi Isaac
                                                  Elazar</addressee></sic>:</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Yesterday I received your delightful letter and I
                                        am sorry that<lb/> I am unable to do your wish. For, all my
                                        days in this land I refrained<lb/> from giving a "Get". This
                                        winter <persName>Dr. Adler</persName>, the Rabbi of
                                                  <placeName>London</placeName> and also<lb/> his
                                        son-in-law, the Rabbi of <placeName>Hamburg</placeName>,
                                        wrote to me about the matter of a<lb/> certain "Get" in
                                                  <placeName>New York</placeName>. And there, too, I
                                        did not grant their request.<lb/> My point of view and my
                                        principle are not to give a "Get", especially at<lb/> this
                                        time, since in <placeName>New York</placeName>, in the Beth
                                        Midrash, there are many scholars<lb/> who want to do such
                                        things.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">And now, my dear friend, because of the crisis in
                                        the country, I<lb/> have been forced to give up my business
                                        now about 6 months, and I have<lb/> been sitting at home as
                                        in my first days. I beg of you to send me through<lb/>
                                        Adam's express, the "Jeshurun" of <persName>Dr.
                                                  Hirsch</persName> for the years<lb/> consisting of
                                        volume 59, 60, and 61. I shall return it to you as soon
                                        as<lb/> possible. If you can do so, it will be a great favor
                                        to me. For the<lb/> past 2 months I have not received the
                                        "Occident". I don't know why. Perhaps<lb/> because I left
                                        home.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">Your faithful friend,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <persName role="author">Abraham Rice</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)"><placeName>Barnet Street # 26</placeName>.</p>
